1. stet] Soracte, to the north of Rome, was distinctly visible from the city, and prominent by its shape. Orelli well remarks that in summer the Italian mountains have a dim and hazy outline, but in winter are clear and well-defined. Hence stet: ‘stands out clear with its white mant-le of snow.’
